{"image_id": "KMB_2006_page_88", "image_size": [1275, 1650], "ocr": [{"text": "KIMBERLY-CLARK CORPORATION AND SUBSIDIARIES", "bbox": [355.7, 158.9, 919.5, 179.7]}, {"text": "NOTES TO CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS—(Continued)", "bbox": [298.1, 196.4, 977.0, 217.2]}, {"text": "Note 14.", "bbox": [162.5, 246.4, 235.4, 267.2]}, {"text": "Synthetic Fuel Partnerships", "bbox": [256.3, 246.4, 504.1, 267.2]}, {"text": "The Corporation has minority interests in two synthetic fuel partnerships. Although these partnerships are", "bbox": [204.2, 284.1, 1112.4, 304.9]}, {"text": "variable interest entities that are subject to the requirements of FIN 46R, the Corporation is not the primary", "bbox": [162.5, 309.1, 1112.3, 329.9]}, {"text": "beneficiary, and the entities have not been consolidated. Synthetic fuel produced by the partnerships is eligible", "bbox": [162.5, 334.1, 1112.3, 354.9]}, {"text": "for synthetic fuel tax credits through 2007. In addition, there are tax deductions for pretax losses generated by the", "bbox": [162.5, 359.1, 1112.4, 379.9]}, {"text": "partnerships that are reported as nonoperating expense in the Corporation’s Consolidated Income Statement.", "bbox": [162.5, 384.1, 1112.3, 404.9]}, {"text": "Both the credits and tax deductions reduce the Corporation’s income tax expense. The tax credits begin to be", "bbox": [162.5, 409.1, 1112.5, 429.9]}, {"text": "phased out as the average annual domestic price of oil exceeds certain statutory amounts. The effects of these", "bbox": [162.5, 434.1, 1112.4, 454.9]}, {"text": "credits and deductions are shown in the following table:", "bbox": [162.5, 459.1, 629.5, 479.9]}, {"text": "Year Ended December 31", "bbox": [797.0, 503.7, 979.9, 520.4]}, {"text": "2006", "bbox": [708.5, 528.7, 741.9, 545.4]}, {"text": "2005", "bbox": [861.4, 528.7, 894.7, 545.4]}, {"text": "2004", "bbox": [1024.6, 528.7, 1057.9, 545.4]}, {"text": "(Millions of dollars)", "bbox": [818.3, 553.7, 958.8, 570.4]}, {"text": "Nonoperating ex